1. c4 e5 2. Nc3 {[%csl Bd5][%cal Gc4d5,Gc3d5] White develops the knight and reinforces the control of the [d5]-square.} Nc6 {Black develops and keeps the options with the f-pawn open.} 3. Nf3 {[%cal Gf3e5,Gf3d4,Gd2d4] As in the majority of cases, White plays for [d4].} g6 {[%csl Bd4][%cal Gf8g7,Rg7d4,Rc6d4] This is a somewhat tricky move order because now White cannot play the Botvinnik Setup recommended in the corresponding chapter – the knight is already on [f3].} 4. d4 {[%cal Gd4e5,Gf3e5] The knight on [f3] also has positive aspects – White can execute the central thrust [d4] before Black fianchettoes the bishop and takes control of the [d4]-square.} exd4 ({Keeping the tension with} 4... d6 {and hoping for a King's Indian set-up is met by} 5. dxe5 Nxe5 {or 5...dxe5 6.Qxd8 Kxd8 7.b3 intending [Bb2] and [O-O-O] with good play for White 6.Bf4 Bg7 7.c5! Nxf3 8.exf3 with initiative in the center.}) ({White reacts similarly to} 4... Bg7 {with} 5. dxe5 Nxe5 6. Nxe5 Bxe5 7. g3 {with easy play after [Bg2], [O-O] thanks to the control of the long diagonal and the central [d5]-square.}) 5. Nxd4 Bg7 ({Black cannot avoid the doubling of the c-pawns as} 5... Nge7 $2 6. Bg5 Bg7 7. Nd5 {wins for White!}) 6. Nxc6 {White doubles Black's c-pawns whichever way Black recaptures.} bxc6 {This is the alternative recapture, but it gives White easy play.} 7. g3 {[%csl Yc6][%cal Gf1g2,Gg2a8] The fianchettoed bishop will be very strong, putting pressure on the [c6]-pawn after Black plays ...[d6].} Ne7 {[%cal Ge7c6,Rd7d6] Black must develop the knight to [e7] in order to have the [c6]-pawn defended. Only then can he play ...[d6], which would allow for the development of the bishop on [c8].} 8. Bg2 {Both sides continue with their development.} O-O 9. O-O d6 10. Bg5 {[%csl Yc6,Ya8][%cal Gd1d2,Ga1d1,Bg2a8] Pinning the knight on [e7] and threatening [Bxc6]. 💡What can we consider of the position? 🔹White has easy development Qd2 and [Rad1] are coming, and there is pressure on the [h1]-[a8] diagonal and the [c6]-pawn; 🔹better pawn structure and space advantage.} *

