{🏆World Blitz Chess Championship, Saint Petersburg, Round 13, December 12, 2018.} 1. c4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Nf3 Nc6 4. e4 Bc5 {As noted in the theoretical chapter, this is the more forcing choice compared to 4...[Bb4].} 5. Nxe5 {The only way for White to play for an advantage.} Nxe5 6. d4 Bb4 7. dxe5 Nxe4 8. Qf3 Nxc3 9. bxc3 Be7 $6 {Today we can say that this is a dubious move, but we know that thanks to games like this one.} 10. Qg3 $1 {[%csl Yg7][%cal Gg3g7] White immediately targets the [g7]-pawn.} g6 ({After} 10... O-O 11. Bh6 g6 12. h4 {gives White a very strong attack.}) 11. Bh6 {[%cal Gh6f8] Black won't be able to castle short, but castling long won't solve his problems either.} d6 {[%cal Gc8e6,Gd8d7,Ge8c8]} 12. Be2 Be6 13. Rd1 {[%cal Gd1d8] White's king will be very safe on the kingside.} Qd7 14. exd6 cxd6 15. O-O O-O-O {Black evacuated the king from the center, but it won't find peace there.} 16. Be3 {[%csl Ya7][%cal Ge3a7,Gc4c5] The bishop did its job on [h6] and is now relocated to a better attacking position. Apart from attacking the [a7]-pawn the bishop also supports the [c5]-advance.} Qa4 {[%csl Ya7][%cal Ga4a7] Black defends the pawn on [a7] and gets away from the pin on the d-file.} 17. Qf3 {[%csl Yb7][%cal Gd1b1,Gb1b7,Gf3b7] The queen wasn't doing much on [g3], so Carlsen improves its position by targeting the [b7]-pawn.} Qc6 18. Qf4 {[%csl Ya7][%cal Ge3a7] With a looming attack, White won't exchange queens. Now that pawn on [a7] hangs again.} b6 19. a4 $1 {[%cal Ga4a5,Ga5b6] Not giving respite! The threat is [a5].} Rd7 ({Taking the pawn leads to a disaster after} 19... Qxa4 $2 20. Ra1 Qd7 21. c5 {and the attack breaks through.}) 20. a5 {[%cal Ga5b6] White continues with the attack.} bxa5 21. Rb1 {[%cal Gb1b8,Ge2f3,Gf3a8,Ge3a7] With the b-file and diagonals open in the vicinity of his king, Black cannot hope to survive for long.} Rc7 22. c5 {[%cal Ge2b5,Ge2f3,Gf4b8,Gb1b8] Opening more diagonals.} dxc5 23. Bf3 $2 {A mistake, but pardonable in blitz.} (23. Bb5 {with [Qa4] next was crushing.}) 23... Qd6 $2 ({The only move to stay in the game was the unexpected} 23... g5 $1 {, but that's another move that is impossible to find in blitz.}) 24. Qe4 {[%csl Ya8][%cal Gf3a8] Now the game is over.} Rd8 (24... Rd8 {Black lost on time, but after} 25. Rb8+ {it's curtains anyway.}) *

